Sequence Information.Peptide Name: Temporin-1SPa  (XXA; UCLL1c; natural AMPs; frog, amphibians, animals)

Literature Information.Literature: Activity: Antinacterial activity was not reported due to a limited amount of material. We filled up this gap by using a synthetic peptide. Active against S. aureus USA300 (MIC 6.3 uM), S. epidermidis 1457 (MIC 6.3 uM), B. subtilis 168 (MIC 12.5 uM), C. albicans (MIC 25 uM), D. glabrata (MIC 25 uM), and  C. tropicalis (6.2 uM) (Mishra, Wang et al. 2018). Updated 5/2018.
Literature Information.Author: Bevier CR, Sonnevend A, Kolodziejek J, Nowotny N, Nielsen PF, Conlon JM.2004
Literature Information.Reference: Comp Biochem Physiol C Toxicol Pharmacol. 2004 Oct;139(1-3):31-8.PubMed
Literature Information.Title: Purification and characterization of antimicrobial peptides from the skin secretions of the mink frog (Rana septentrionalis).
